"{\"abstract\":\"Most artificial intelligence (AI) based learning systems act in virtual or laboratory environments. Here we demonstrate an AI-based curling robot system named \\u2018Curly\\u2019 that competes on a real-world curling ice sheet. Curly encompasses (1) an AI-based curling strategy and simulation engine under consideration of the high \\u2018icy\\u2019 uncertainty, (2) the thrower robot enabled by autonomous driving with traction control, and (3) the skip robot that allows to recognize the curling field and stone configuration based on vision technology. The Curly performed well both: in classical game situations and when interacting with human opponents, namely, the top-ranked Korean amateur high school curling team.\",\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"2175047\",\"name\":\"Dong-Ok Won\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/2175047\"},{\"authorId\":\"2399550\",\"name\":\"Byung-Do Kim\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/2399550\"},{\"authorId\":\"48206675\",\"name\":\"H. Kim\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/48206675\"},{\"authorId\":\"51055789\",\"name\":\"Tae-San Eom\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/51055789\"},{\"authorId\":\"145034054\",\"name\":\"K. M\\u00fcller\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/145034054\"},{\"authorId\":\"1703007\",\"name\":\"S. Lee\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/1703007\"}],\"citationVelocity\":0,\"citations\":[{\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"146142995\",\"name\":\"Asiain Neno\"},{\"authorId\":\"145700038\",\"name\":\"J. Esteban\"}],\"doi\":null,\"intent\":[\"background\"],\"isInfluential\":false,\"paperId\":\"b97990f7f1a7985b682edb154a971852eb720e70\",\"title\":\"Integraci\\u00f3n de m\\u00e9todos de inteligencia artificial y procesamiento de im\\u00e1genes para jugar ajedrez en el robot Baxter\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/b97990f7f1a7985b682edb154a971852eb720e70\",\"venue\":\"\",\"ye